Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Boil your #kettle{}, then pour the @boiled water{500%ml} into a #measuring jug{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Add the @British chicken breast{260%g}(diced) and @garlic paste{} to the pan and fry for ~{1%minute}. Add the @risotto rice{175%g}, stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Add the @cider vinegar{15%ml}, and stir until evaporated, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{20%g} and bring back to the boil, then pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with foil). Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} and pop them onto a piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Drizzle over the @honey{1%tbsp}.

Fold the foil, sealing on all sides to create a parcel. Pop onto a large #baking tray{} and roast on the bottom shelf until softened, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Drain the @mozzarella{1%ball} and squeeze out as much liquid as you can. Pat dry with #kitchen paper{}, then tear into small pieces.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and mix in the @butter{20%g}, @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}, @baby spinach{40%g} and @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}.

Season to taste with salt and pepper if needed.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Change your oven setting to grill and set to the highest temperature.

Arrange the mozzarella on top of your risotto.

Grill until golden and bubbling, ~{5-8%minutes}.

Share your risotto between your #bowls{}, then top with your roasted baby plum tomatoes (discard the juices) and drizzle over the @fresh pesto{32%g} to finish. Enjoy!